<a name="download_options"><h2>Download Options</h2></a>
<h3>Download FASTA</h3>
Download the sequnece of selected transcript(s) (FASTA format)<br>
<h3>Download BLAST</h3>
Download the blast results of selected transcript(s) against reference protein (TSV format)<br>
<h4>Output description</h4>
tool: blast tool name<br>
query_name: transcript sequence name<br>
hit_name: reference protein accession<br>
query_length: the length of the query sequence<br>
query_hsp_start: offset of query at the start of the alignment (one-offset)<br>
query_hsp_end: offset of query at the end of the alignment (one-offset)<br>
query_strand: the strand direction of the query sequence if applicable<br>
query_frame: frame of the query if applicable<br>
hit_length: the length of the reference sequence<br>
hit_hsp_start: offset of reference at the start of the alignment (one-offset)<br>
hit_hsp_end: offset of reference at the end of the alignment (one-offset)<br>
hit_strand: the strand direction of the reference sequence if applicable<br>
hit_frame: frame of the reference if applicable<br>
hsp_score: score (in bits) of the HSP<br>
hsp_bits: number of bits for that score<br>
hsp_evalue: expect value of the HSP<br>
hsp_length: length of the alignment<br>
hsp_gaps: number of gaps in the alignment<br>
hsp_identities: number of identities in the alignment<br>
hsp_identity_percent: percentage of identities in the alignment<br>
hsp_positives: number of positive (conservative) substitutions in the alignment<br>
hsp_positive_percent: percentage of positive (conservative) substitutions in the alignment<br>
query_coverage: the alignment coverage of the query sequence<br>
hit_coverage: the alignment coverage of the reference protein<br>
hit_description: the description of the reference protein<br>

<h3>Download Gene Expression</h3>
Download the rpkm data of selected transcripts(s) (TSV format)
<h4>Output description</h4>
feature_id: transcript sequence name<br>
gene_length: transcript sequence length<br>
ss_rpkm: the RPKM value with susceptible reads mapped to reference<br>
rs_rpkm: the RPKM value with resistant reads mapped to reference<br>
rc_rpkm: the PRKM value with recovered reads mapped to reference<br>
rs_ss_ratio: rs_rpkm / ss_rpkm<br>
rs_rc_ratio: rs_rpkm / rc_rpkm<br>
expression: up if both rs_ss_ratio and rs_rc_ratio are greater than 2; down if both are less than 0.5<br>
line: the line of the transcript<br>
insecticide: the type of insecticide of the mapped reads<br>
annotation: the description of the reference protein<br>

